5:
That was super tasty! Thanks for the
snacks again, today!
9: Remember to brush your teeth, Fuku.
18:
Fuku seems to be getting quite
comfortable with Starview Village.
22:
She was really jumpy at first, but
recently she's been smiling a lot
more.
26:
Yes, but... I am concerned about
something.
29:
Fuku often goes out on her own and
sometimes doesn't return for several
days.
32:
Yeah... She is a yokai, though. Pretty
par for the course, don't you think?
36:
But she's still so young. She should
be safe in Starview Village, but I
worry about her safety anywhere
else.
38:
I think it's only right that I be her
guardian.
42:
Really? I wonder what she'd say to
that...
45:
It seems like she had a rough
experience with people in the past.
We should see how she feels about
having a guardian.
49: Indeed. I will go and speak with her.
53:
What's wrong, Light? Did you wanna
ask me something?
56:
Oh, not really... I was just thinking it
would be nice if we got you your
own room.
59:
Breaking and entering other
people's homes perhaps isn't the
best nighttime routine, wouldn't you
agree?
62:
Since you seem to have adjusted to
life in Starview, maybe it's time for
you to have a place of your own to—
129:
I... I just thought she might like to
have her own room!
135:
Don't worry, Fuku. We won't imprison
you.
140: I... I know... But, I just...
145:
Did those people lock you away in
the past?
148:
Humans think keeping me in their
house will bring them good luck...
151:
So they used a talisman to seal me
away in a room... I was trapped in
there for so long...
158:
After a very long time I finally
managed to escape, but... I can't go
back to that...
161: Fuku. I'm so sorry for what I said.
165:
No, it's okay... I'm sorry too. So
everything's okay now.
171:
Good luck or not, it's simply
inhuman how they could lock up a
yokai child like yourself...
175:
From now on, we will accompany
you whenever you head out—
192:
I'm what's called a zashiki
warashi—a yokai with a childlike
appearance. No matter how old I
get, I always look the same.
202:
It does. In terms of age, you're like a
teeny-tiny baby brother to me, Light!
207:
I... I see. I suppose it was wrong of
me to worry for you.
212:
You don't need to be sorry! I was
just... a little bit surprised!
216:
But if you want me here... Then I'm
happy.
220: In that case, so am I.
225:
If you ever do want your own room,
feel free to ask anytime!
227:
We'll get you a room so nice you'll
forget all about those bad
experiences you had!
